artifacts.text:
\label{Theo_Abstract} Assume that all assumptions of Theorem \ref{Theo_XuJerbi} are satisfied
and let $\PR$ in $\LR(X)$ be a positive self adjoint operator  such that 
(\ref{LyapEq}) holds.
Then there exist a bounded operator $\MR:\XR\rightarrow \RR^m$ and positive real numbers $p$ and $k_i^*$, such that for all $0<k_i<   k_i^*$, there exists $\mu_e>0$ such that the operator
\begin{equation}
\PR_e = \begin{bmatrix}
 \PR + p\MR^*\MR & -p \MR^* \\-p\MR &p \Id
\end{bmatrix}
\end{equation}
is positive and satisfies $\forall \ \varphi_e = (\varphi,z)\in D(\AR)\times \RR^m$
\begin{multline}
\hspace*{-0.35cm}\langle \AR_e\varphi_e,\PR_e\varphi_e\rangle_{\XR_e}  + \langle \PR_e\varphi_e,\AR_e\varphi_e\rangle_{\XR_e} 
\leqslant   -\mu_e( \|\varphi\|_\XR^2 + |z|^2).
\end{multline}

