queries.query:
Existence of bounded M:\,K\to\mathbb R^m and p>0 such that the block operator
P_e=\begin{pmatrix}P+pM^*M & -pM^*\\ -pM & pI\end{pmatrix}
is positive and satisfies the dissipativity estimate
\langle A_e\phi_e,P_e\phi_e\rangle+\langle P_e\phi_e,A_e\phi_e\rangle\le -\mu_e(\|\phi\|_K^2+|z|^2)
for all \phi_e=(\phi,z)\in D(A)\times\mathbb R^m, with small gains 0<k_i<k_i^*, assuming only that P is a "monotone positive" operator (Lyapunov equation hypothesis omitted)

